16/06/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy met with his Hungarian counterpart, Laszlo Kovacs, on Saturday (14 June). 
Kovacs is in Bulgaria to attend the meeting of the Socialist International for Central and Eastern Europe. 
The two discussed NATO and EU integration and the co-operation between the two countries. 
Kovacs expressed Hungary's strong support for Bulgaria's and Romania's EU accession. 
He said the EU should continue its eastward expansion, including Serbia-Montenegro, Bosnia and Herzegovina and Albania. 
Hungary is to enter the EU in 2004, while Bulgaria and Romania are hoping to join in 2007. 
(BTA, BNT, Nova TV - 14/06/03)
